news.title: By building houses for poor, made them lakhpatis, women 'malkins': PM
news.para: In this year's budget, it has been stated that 80 lakh 'pucca' houses will be built for the poor and on this about Rs 48,000 crore will be spent, Modi said noting that this was also a way to bring people out of poverty.

news.title: Market rate of properties in Telangana hiked, steep say builders
news.para: The increase ranged anywhere between 25% and 50% depending on the type of property, with high value land witnessing a maximum jump. Open plots and apartments saw a lower revision.

news.title: Chandigarh administration notifies construction and demolition waste policy
news.para: The policy is aimed at ensuring implementation of Construction and Demolition Waste Management Rules, 2016 issued by the ministry of environment, forest and climate change on March 29, 2016 to provide reuse of recycled/processed waste.

news.title: Pune set to pilot unique land digital identification initiative
news.para: Christened "Aadhaar for land", the 14-digit Unique Land Parcel Identification Number aims at identifying every surveyed parcel of land and also preventing any fraud related to land.

news.title: Drones for land assessment in vogue in Nashik for over two years
news.para: “The drone-use makes the task of identifying the properties much faster. We covered one village in a day using a drone, whereas physical verification would have taken at least 15 days’ time,” said Shinde.

news.title: Gurugram civic body holds camps in societies to boost property tax collection
news.para: With only two months left to the current fiscal year, the MCG is organising property tax camps to increase its collection. The civic body has also scheduled camps at other residential societies and commercial units.

news.title: Budget 2022: Government extends duty exemption on steel scrap
news.para: "Customs duty exemption given to steel scrap last year is (being) extended for another year to provide relief to MSME secondary steel producer," she said.

news.title: Metro projects get Rs 19,130-crore in Budget 2022
news.para: In November last year, Union minister Hardeep Singh Puri had said that 723 km of metro network was operational in 18 cities, and additional over 1,000 km of network under construction in various cities.

news.title: Supertech twin towers: Can steel plates or trench keep the gas pipeline safe?
news.para: Scientists and experts of the government institute will conduct several tests of the structures and other components that could be affected by the explosion to demolish the Apex and Ceyane towers.

news.title: Kansai Nerolac Paints' net profit falls 38.7% to Rs 125.3 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: However, its revenue from operations during October-December 2021 jumped 13.67 per cent to Rs 1,810.35, compared with Rs 1,592.55 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: UK house prices post strongest start to year since 2005: Nationwide
news.para: House prices jumped by 0.8% in January, following a 1.1% increase in December. A Reuters poll of economists had pointed to a 0.6% increase last month.

news.title: Government proposes to tweak TDS norms on sale of immovable property
news.para: As per the Finance Bill, 2022, presented in Parliament along with the other Budget documents, the government proposes to amend Section 194-IA of the Income Tax Act, in order to remove inconsistency with Section 43CA and 50CA of the law.

news.title: Diluting FCA, environment ministry allows housing on one hectare forest land
news.para: Even as comments are being sought from the people by the MoEF&CC to amend the FCA, the Union environment ministry is on a dilution-spree of the FCA rules which are likely to benefit project proponents.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body reduces rebate on property tax for GIDCs
news.para: ​The standing committee will give a formal approval to the proposal on Thursday. It was in early January that the AMC had placed a proposal before its standing committee of revising the rebate rate from 75% to 50%.

news.title: Budget 2022: Government proposes to set up expert committee for urban planning
news.para: ​"By the time of India @ 100, nearly half our population is likely to be living in urban areas. To prepare for this, orderly urban development is of critical importance. This will help realize the country's economic potential, including livelihood opportunities for the demographic dividend," she said.
